info.name: BottomSidebar TabsPreview Dock
info.description:
using this style and the "Showcase" addon >
https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/showcase/?src=ss you can -
move the Sidebar horizzontally to the Bottom - 
add the gradient colors background -
add the dock -
show the tabs tumbnails with a ZoomIn effect on hovering the mini blue sidebar at center bottom and ZoomOut on focus lost -

If you don't care about the search box as I did open about:config and set the integer value
extensions.showcase.sidebarFindBarMode to 2
info.additionalInfo:
the dock is the mix of two of mine:
SpotLightDock > http://www.wincustomize.com/explore/objectdock/16956/ 
and NeonDock > http://www.wincustomize.com/explore/objectdock_backgrounds/368/
For the Sidebar at Top go here > http://userstyles.org/styles/94040/topsidebar-tabspreview-dock
Thanks to deft  > http://userstyles.org/styles/91562/auto-hide-sidebar-for-firefox-default-style
and dotter Ben  > http://userstyles.org/styles/8817/firefox-showcase-custom-backgroun
special thanks to hideheader for the help to exclude the other Sidebars (Bookmarks, History, Stylish etc.)
